real_t gpx::phy::NewtonPlasticityData::e

Elasticity.

Common values lie inside [1.0, 2.0] interval. Edge cases:

  • 1.0 - perfectly in-elastic.
  • 2.0 - perfectly elastic (preserved kinetic energy).

real_t gpx::phy::NewtonPlasticityData::s

Stickiness.

Common values lie inside [0.0, 2.0] interval. Edge cases:

  • 0.0 - perfectly frictionless,
  • 1.0 - perfectly sticky,
  • 2.0 - perfectly resilient.

Note:
this parameter is not self-sufficient and it may be affected by friction coefficients.
